    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\ni_ctrl-u will delete all the text before the cursor, when using nvim_buf_set_text.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n* nvim --clean\r\n* `so test.lua`\r\n* `<c-u>`\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nlocal api = vim.api\r\n\r\nlocal winid = api.nvim_get_current_win()\r\nlocal bufnr = api.nvim_win_get_buf(winid)\r\n\r\nlocal prefix = \"hello\"\r\napi.nvim_buf_set_lines(bufnr, 0, 1, false, { prefix })\r\napi.nvim_win_set_cursor(winid, { 1, #prefix })\r\n\r\nvim.cmd.startinsert()\r\n\r\nlocal placeholder = \" world\"\r\napi.nvim_buf_set_text(bufnr, 0, #prefix, 0, #prefix, { placeholder })\r\n\r\napi.nvim_win_set_cursor(winid, { 1, #prefix + #placeholder })\r\n```\r\n\r\nthis script tries to do the same as `ihello<esc>a world`, and i think i'm doing it right.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\ni_ctrl-u deletes ` world` rather than `hello world`\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.9.1\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\narchlinux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nst 0.9\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nst-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nsystem package manager",
    "closed_at": "2023-08-10T11:30:26Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "You need `bang = true` so the start of the insertion is after the text, and `vim.schedule()` the edit in Insert mode:\r\n```lua\r\nlocal api = vim.api\r\n\r\nlocal winid = api.nvim_get_current_win()\r\nlocal bufnr = api.nvim_win_get_buf(winid)\r\n\r\nlocal prefix = \"hello\"\r\napi.nvim_buf_set_lines(bufnr, 0, 1, false, { prefix })\r\napi.nvim_win_set_cursor(winid, { 1, #prefix })\r\n\r\nvim.cmd.startinsert({ bang = true })\r\n\r\nvim.schedule(function()\r\n  local placeholder = \" world\"\r\n  api.nvim_buf_set_text(bufnr, 0, #prefix, 0, #prefix, { placeholder })\r\n\r\n  api.nvim_win_set_cursor(winid, { 1, #prefix + #placeholder })\r\nend)\r\n```",
